item.title: Dramatic video: NSW dam bursts its banks
item.description: Dramatic footage has shown a NSW dam bursting its banks after heavy rainfall drenched the state over the weekend.

item.title: Cops filmed storming illegal beach rave
item.description: Video has shown an “unruly and hostile” crowd booing at police as a beach rave was broken up in Far North Queensland over the weekend.

item.title: Surfer dies after being dragged under drain
item.description: A man died while surfing in treacherous conditions along the northern beaches of Sydney this afternoon.

item.title: Heartfelt open letter to Victorian nurses
item.description: Australian College of Nursing chief executive Professor Kylie Ward has penned a heartfelt open letter to nurses across Victoria as healthcare workers battle fatigue.

item.title: Letter exposes Vic outbreak bungle
item.description: New evidence has found the federal aged care watchdog was aware of an outbreak of COVID-19 at a Melbourne nursing home but didn’t alert the Department of Health for four days.

item.title: ‘Serious’ criminal dies in detention
item.description: A man with a “very serious criminal history” and who was set to be deported has died while being held at an immigration detention centre in Melbourne.

item.title: ‘Agonising’: Virus passes grim milestone
item.description: Australia’s chief medical officer has described Victoria’s situation as “agonising” despite the state’s welcome drop in new infections.

item.title: Funa picks league over tennis to Manly’s benefit
item.description: Tevita Funa is lighting up Manly’s backline with his fleet-footed skills, but the freakish rookie back has revealed he could have pursued a career in tennis.

item.title: State borders to stay closed past Christmas
item.description: Scott Morrison has declared his “hope” that COVID-19 border restrictions will be eased by Christmas but warned Australians it was unlikely that normal movement without any restrictions will be restored by summer.

item.title: Victoria COVID-19 Ads – Sam
item.description: The Victorian government has launched an ad blitz highlighting the dangers of the coronavirus in a bid to bust myths surrounding the highly contagious disease. In one of the ads, couple Sarah and Sam, who are both midwives at Royal Women’s Hospital in the inner northern Melbourne suburb of Parkville, tell of how they were ravaged by the disease.
